race.comment: IT'S A WONDER (4) loomed up on the corner but ran out of condition when resuming over this distance at the Kensington track last start. Down in class today so although her second-up record is not great she looks well placed to play a major role. MAMUSHKA (9) has raced three times this prep, all in shorter races, and found the line for minor placings on each occasion. New to this trip but she is a lightly raced mare with McDonald to steer which is a positive sign. JUST GLAMOUROUS (2) was out-sprinted first-up at Warwick Farm but should be more effective today out to this distance in an easier race. ECLAIR ENCORE (14) resumed with a gutsy win at Newcastle recently. May need more ground now but is not out of contention. MISS HADES (5) is a good fresh performer back from a 19-week spell. Trialling in good style and looks well and truly up for this. Something for the Multiples: NANTUCKET ISLAND (10)
